author: julianfoad
msg: Remove the redundant 'force' parameter from svn_client_move6().  It has been
ignored since svn_client_move5() was introduced.  The functionality of
'move' was changed in r860885 and r861421 so that it moves the source tree
just as it is, even if it contains modified and/or unversioned items.
(move): Don't pass along the 'force' parameter - ignore it.
(svn_client_move5): Document the redundancy of the 'force' parameter.
(svn_client_move6): Remove the 'force' parameter. Adjust the calls to
(svn_cl__move): Don't pass along the 'force' option - ignore it.

author: fdmanana
msg: Replicator fix: for a filtered replication, the replication ID should take into account the filter function's code and not only its name.
